<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Journey to the UK</title></head><body style="background:#ffffff"><div><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Refugee Action (JRR 0001)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="font-weight:normal; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 17pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#b0b61a; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:14pt">Introduction </span><span style="color:#b0b61a; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:14pt">to Refugee Action</span></h2><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 32.81pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Refugee Action is an independent, national charity working to enable refugees to build new lives in the UK. We provide practical support for newly arrived asylum seekers as well as a long-term commitment to their settlement. Through our ‘One Stop Service’,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Choices Assisted Voluntary Return (AVR) Service and </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Gateway Protection Programme, the Home Office funds us to give confidential, independent and non-directive advice and information to asylum seekers, refugees and irregular migrants on a breadth of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">topics. We also offer support through a range of independently funded projects.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.81pt; padding-left:3.19pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Over the last </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">two</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">years, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Refugee Action has:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 54pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">interve</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ned</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> in the case of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">MK &amp; AH v Secretary of State for the Home Department [2012] EWHC 1896 (Admin</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">found that the failure of the Home Office to provide access to support for asylum seekers waiting for a decision on their further claim for asylum for a minimum of three weeks </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">led</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> to homelessness and destitution.</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 54pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">commenced legal proceedings against the Ho</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">me Office to challenge the level of financial support paid to people seeking asylum. The essence of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">this judicial review</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> is that the amount paid to destitute individuals and families (including those with children) is unlawful because it is insufficient to</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> meet their essential living needs or to provide a dignified standard of living.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 32.81pt; padding-left:3.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">In brief, w</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">e believe the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Ministry of Justice’s (MoJ) </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">current proposals </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">outlined in ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Judicial Review: Proposals for further reform</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">’ </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">will limit </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">our ability to take such action </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">in the future</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> for the purpose of holding statutory bodies to account,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">and</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> will restrict access to justice for our beneficiaries.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 32.81pt; padding-left:3.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Refugee</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> Action is grateful for th</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> opportunity to contribute to the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Joint Committee on Human Rights</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">(JCHR) inquiry</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> on </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">judicia</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">l review</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> We have been engaged with the Government’s attempts to re-think access to legal aid because of the impact we believe it will have on our beneficiaries</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> who are asylum seekers, refugees and irregular migrants</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. We have previously responded to the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Mo</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">J</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">’s consultation on ‘Transforming Legal Aid’, the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">JCHR</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> consultation on</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The implications for access to justice of the Government's proposed legal aid reforms</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">’ and The Low Commission’s consultation on ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Developing a strategy for access to advice and </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">support on Social Welfare Law in England and Wales</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">’.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 7pt 32.81pt; padding-left:3.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">We have grouped our response</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> under the heading</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s used </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">in the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">MoJ’s </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">consultation document’s table of contents</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-famil